name:     Actu    Macron insists 'Russia cannot win' Ukraine war In a TV interview, the French president explained how France intends to continue supporting Ukraine, following his controversial statement on the possibility of deploying troops. 
content:In an interview on France 2 on Thursday, March 14, French President Emmanuel Macron explained the stakes involved in supporting Ukraine, after his controversial remarks on the possibility of sending Western troops to face what he called an increasingly "threatening" Russia in Europe."If Russia wins this war, Europe's credibility would be reduced to zero," said Macron. "If Russia were to win, the lives of French people would change," he insisted.